We found this great bar and grill while celebrating my birthday on Saturday, February 13, 2021. It just so happened they had the UFC Welterweight Championship fights that night, which my husband and I enjoy watching. We paid the $10 cover charge and we're given large syringes filled with Jello Shots for free. We found a cozy booth with a flat screen all to ourselves. I had margaritas and my husband loves his Corona, which they had in stock. I ordered their dry rub wings and honestly they were the best I've eaten. I also got thdit house salad which had freshly fried bacon, cheese, eggs and red onion with the Homemade Ranch. My husband had their hamburger which had two huge patties and real house fries. It was a great atmosphere. Laid back with great upbeat music before the fights. I wish we lived closer, but Florida isn't too far away. About three hours. So I would recommend if you're in the area. The take kitchen orders until 12:30 which was great after having a few drinks.
